======================
         BASE URL
======================
http://localhost:8000/api/

======================
        Test API
======================

GET /test/
- Test endpoint to verify server is running.


======================
      Loan App API
======================

1. Get Loan Account by ID  
GET /loan/loan-accounts/{id}/  
Example: /loan/loan-accounts/6/

2. Check Loan Account  
POST /loan/check-loan-account/

3. Get Loan Data by Parameters  
GET /loan/loan-account/  
Query Params: mobileNumber, panNumber, aadharNumber, loanAccountNumber  
Example:  
  /loan/loan-account/?mobileNumber=&panNumber=&aadharNumber=&loanAccountNumber=LN123456789122

4. Get Recent Loan Payment  
GET /loan/recent_loan-payment  
Query Params: loanAccount, loanId  
Example:  
  /loan/recent_loan-payment?loanAccount=&loanId=L123

5. Customer Login Search
POST /loan/customer_login/
======================
     User App API
======================

üë§ AUTH & USER MANAGEMENT

1. Register a New User  
POST /users/

2. Login  
POST /users/login/

3. Logout  
POST /users/logout/

4. Refresh Token  
POST /users/token/refresh/

5. Reset Password  
POST /users/reset-password/  
Example: http://localhost:8000/api/users/reset-password/

6. Search Users  
GET /users/search/?query=

7. Get All Registered Users  
GET /users/

8. Get User by ID  
GET /users/{id}/  
Example: /users/1/

9. Edit User  
PUT /users/{id}/  
Example: /users/3/

10. Delete User  
DELETE /users/{id}/  
Example: /users/3/

11. Count Users  
GET /users/count/


üóùÔ∏è SESSION MANAGEMENT

12. Create Session  
POST /users/sessions/  
Body:
{
  "user_id": 1,
  "joining_date": "2025-06-06",
  "months": 3
}

13. Regenerate Session Key  
PUT /users/sessions/regenerate-key/{id}/  
Example: /users/sessions/regenerate-key/1/

14. Update Session Status  
PUT /users/sessions/update-status/{id}/  
Example: /users/sessions/update-status/1/  
Body:
{
  "is_active": true
}

15. Renew Session  
PUT /users/sessions/renew-session/{id}/  
Example: /users/sessions/renew-session/1/  
Body:
{
  "joining_date": "2025-06-06",
  "months": 2
}
